didn't smoke in his day?

32:44.463 --> 32:45.806
That he still doesn't?

32:56.349 --> 32:57.933
You know, Mom's right.

32:57.934 --> 32:59.436
We're, uh...

33:00.437 --> 33:01.937
We're gonna deal.

33:01.938 --> 33:03.481
I promise.

33:21.208 --> 33:23.131
- So what did you say?

33:24.169 --> 33:26.378
- Does it matter?

33:26.379 --> 33:28.757
- Maybe I want to know
how you lie.

33:30.675 --> 33:32.343
- Wow.

33:32.344 --> 33:33.385
- The usual?

33:33.386 --> 33:34.729
- Thanks.
- And you?

33:34.730 --> 33:38.942
- Uh, coffee and lox platter,
everything bagel.

33:42.229 --> 33:43.938
- Why "wow"?

33:43.939 --> 33:47.068
- It's-it was just a strong
statement, that's all.

33:47.069 --> 33:49.902
- What do you want from me, Sam?

33:49.903 --> 33:51.530
- This.

33:52.405 --> 33:53.989
Right now.

33:53.990 --> 33:55.324
- Like your bagel.

33:55.325 --> 33:56.617
- My bagel?

33:56.618 --> 33:58.040
- Everything.

34:02.958 --> 34:04.833
- Is there coffee?

34:04.834 --> 34:06.544
- Oh, I thought you left.

34:06.545 --> 34:08.842
- I pushed my first meeting
half an hour.

34:08.844 --> 34:11.715
Not sure the girl
will show anyway.

34:11.716 --> 34:13.842
- Who is she?

34:13.842 --> 34:16.266
- Graduate student
I was telling you about.

34:16.266 --> 34:18.222
Brilliant but troubled.

34:18.223 --> 34:19.348
- How?

34:19.349 --> 34:20.851
- Not sure.

34:21.851 --> 34:24.228
Inscrutable.

34:27.649 --> 34:28.899
- Eat out tonight?

34:28.900 --> 34:31.735
- I'm hosting
the seminar dinner.

34:31.735 --> 34:34.362
- I hate the thought of you
walking home so late.

34:34.364 --> 34:36.447
- I'll be quiet coming in.

34:43.956 --> 34:45.373
- I might be up.

34:45.375 --> 34:47.918
- Yeah?

35:09.899 --> 35:12.151
- <i>The first time
I came to New York,</i>

35:12.152 --> 35:15.372
this is where my mum took us
before anywhere else.

35:15.373 --> 35:17.948
I was so pissed.

35:17.949 --> 35:19.542
- Why?
- Where did you want to go?

35:19.543 --> 35:21.201
- Shops, noise,

35:21.202 --> 35:24.079
the huge buildings,

35:24.080 --> 35:25.205
theaters, streets.

35:25.206 --> 35:27.416
Wha-whatever.

35:27.417 --> 35:28.417
- That doesn't sound like you.

35:28.418 --> 35:30.796
- Yeah, but then when
we got there, I was like,

35:30.797 --> 35:33.264
"Oh, <i>I</i> get it."

35:34.257 --> 35:35.802
- You'll have to tell her
you went.

35:35.803 --> 35:37.801
- "Oh, that's so sweet, darling.

35:37.802 --> 35:39.016
Who'd you go with?"

35:39.017 --> 35:41.140
- You don't have to tell her
with whom.

35:41.141 --> 35:43.813
- She says I'm having the life
she never had the guts to.

35:43.814 --> 35:45.225
- A career.

35:45.226 --> 35:46.352
- Oh, bigger than that.

35:46.353 --> 35:48.697
Like, she's never
had a place of her own.

35:48.698 --> 35:50.564
Imagine that.

35:50.565 --> 35:54.485
From her parents to college
and then in with Dad.

35:54.486 --> 35:58.081
And of course, I have yet to
live the only life she's known.

35:58.082 --> 36:00.366
- Well, would you want that?

36:00.367 --> 36:02.660
- I-I'm as.

36:02.661 --> 36:04.789
- Friends of mine are having
their kids in their 40s.

36:04.790 --> 36:06.631
- And they'll be in
their 60s when their kids

36:06.632 --> 36:07.748
graduate college.

36:07.749 --> 36:08.921
Not for me.

36:10.293 --> 36:11.794
You need to know that.

36:11.795 --> 36:13.545
- You've made that clear.

36:13.546 --> 36:14.546
- It doesn't seem like it.

36:14.547 --> 36:16.049
- Okay.

36:17.175 --> 36:19.018
We have four days together.

36:19.886 --> 36:21.138
Three and a half.

36:22.138 --> 36:25.432
We agreed that we-
and now twice this morning.

36:25.433 --> 36:26.434
- I'm sorry.

36:27.435 --> 36:28.435
- I'll do right by us.

36:32.232 --> 36:34.360
I just don't know
what that means.

36:34.361 --> 36:36.902
- Can't that be good?

36:36.903 --> 36:38.987
<i>Not knowing?</i>

36:54.629 --> 36:56.552
- It just seems so irrelevant.

36:58.258 --> 37:01.055
Arguing interpretations
with the other 12 people

37:01.056 --> 37:02.803
that have read
the same text as you.

37:02.804 --> 37:05.180
- Millions would be
more accurate.

37:05.181 --> 37:06.890
- Not these days.

37:06.891 --> 37:08.562
- Something must've kept
you interested

37:08.563 --> 37:10.312
through a master's program.

37:14.190 --> 37:16.275
<i>You become accustomed.</i>

37:16.276 --> 37:18.694
- To abject despair?

37:18.695 --> 37:22.074
- To choosing a life that
relates directly to very few,

37:22.075 --> 37:24.241
but quite directly to everyone.

37:24.242 --> 37:26.118
- What if you're fooling
yourself?

37:26.119 --> 37:28.838
- That very question is what
it's all about.

37:28.839 --> 37:30.247
- Fooling ourselves?

37:30.248 --> 37:32.463
- At the heart
of human interaction

37:32.464 --> 37:35.838
is the agreement that
we're all going to fabricate.

37:35.839 --> 37:39.135
Which is to say, agree on
certain precepts we call truths,

37:39.136 --> 37:42.887
but would be utter nonsense
to anyone not in on the game.

37:42.888 --> 37:44.887
Consider language.

37:44.888 --> 37:48.307
We call an elephant an elephant

37:48.308 --> 37:51.903
with a certainty that will
go so far as to marginalize,

37:51.904 --> 37:54.646
even ostracize
those who will refuse.

37:54.647 --> 37:58.734
Society depends zealously
on this, so we can structure it.

37:58.735 --> 38:02.362
In this case,
communicate with one another

38:02.363 --> 38:05.032
even as each of us
has his or her own

38:05.033 --> 38:08.368
disposition toward elephants.

38:08.369 --> 38:11.248
Why should philosophy
in any form be different?

38:11.249 --> 38:13.212
- Because ultimately
who really cares?

38:13.213 --> 38:16.255
- Everyone, regardless
of how few want to try

38:16.256 --> 38:19.802
to understand it, which is why
I've spent my life gorgeously

38:19.803 --> 38:21.220
and so can you.

38:49.410 --> 38:52.084
- Why have you done this
to yourself, Sophie?

38:52.085 --> 38:54.833
- To know that I'm here.

38:57.418 --> 38:59.386
- May I ask how?

39:00.588 --> 39:02.340
- Curling iron mostly.

39:07.303 --> 39:09.681
- If to be wounded
is to exist...

39:10.765 --> 39:13.769
You're giving yourself
a pretty narrow endgame.

39:17.188 --> 39:20.148
- Have you sought counseling?

39:20.149 --> 39:22.192
Been to health services?

39:22.193 --> 39:24.912
- There is a woman that
I've started to see, yeah.

39:26.114 --> 39:28.116
- Is she aware of this?

39:30.451 --> 39:32.920
You have to tell her.

39:38.668 --> 39:40.420
- Will you come with me?

39:48.469 --> 39:51.266
- No, Mr. Cohen already
makes me paranoid enough.

39:51.267 --> 39:53.060
- But that's two hours from now,

39:53.061 --> 39:54.396
and besides, he's harmless.

39:54.397 --> 39:56.732
All you have to do
is use the word "dichotomy"

39:56.733 --> 39:58.192
and he'll eat out of your hand.

39:58.193 --> 40:00.610
- I still don't know
what that word means.

40:00.611 --> 40:02.733
- He actually misuses it.

40:02.734 --> 40:04.907
Specifically it's the rhetorical
contrasting of two opposing

40:04.908 --> 40:07.493
or divergent ideas,
thus the prefix dicho-, two,

40:07.494 --> 40:09.489
and then -tomy, meaning to cut.

40:09.490 --> 40:11.083
- Make out with me.

40:25.048 --> 40:26.298
Hal?

40:26.299 --> 40:27.767
- Yeah?

40:29.844 --> 40:32.220
- I think I'm ready.

40:32.221 --> 40:35.350
This weekend my parents
will be away.

40:37.268 --> 40:39.811
- Is it 'cause
my mom has cancer?

40:39.812 --> 40:41.813
- No, asshole.

40:44.150 --> 40:45.238
It's because I want to.

40:45.239 --> 40:47.277
- So it's not a sympathy thing?

40:48.279 --> 40:49.743
You ask me that one more time,

40:49.744 --> 40:52.993
we're breaking up and you can
keep fucking your hand.

40:53.993 --> 40:55.827
- Wow.

40:55.828 --> 40:57.123
Friday might be tricky,

40:57.124 --> 40:59.590
but I can just tell my parents
I'm staying at Greg's.

41:04.379 --> 41:06.922
- <i>I could spend a year
like this.</i>

41:06.923 --> 41:08.095
<i>Every day.</i>

41:10.385 --> 41:12.137
How do you fit it
all into a life?

41:12.138 --> 41:15.231
- You leave the world
with things still to do.

41:15.232 --> 41:16.306
- That's tragic.

41:16.307 --> 41:18.517
- Tragic is becoming satisfied.

41:19.519 --> 41:21.567
Why didn't I meet you
20 years ago?

41:21.568 --> 41:24.106
- Mm, the Atlantic Ocean.

41:24.107 --> 41:25.825
Child abuse.

41:26.818 --> 41:28.286
- Where's that one from?

41:28.287 --> 41:29.904
- Malaysia.

41:31.864 --> 41:33.240
- This shape is incredible.

41:33.241 --> 41:34.700
- Mm.

41:34.701 --> 41:37.869
The lower and upper sepals
are for protection.

41:37.870 --> 41:40.080
This petal is the labellum.

41:40.081 --> 41:41.545
It's always the largest.

41:41.546 --> 41:45.132
It lies flat like that to make
it comfortable for pollinators.

41:45.133 --> 41:48.588
All that beauty is-is just
about making more of them.

41:48.589 --> 41:49.590
- Right.

41:50.591 --> 41:51.925
- Sam?

41:51.926 --> 41:54.179
- You've got to be kidding me.
- What is it?

41:54.180 --> 41:55.805
- That's my daughter's teacher.

41:56.806 --> 41:59.683
- Teddy, I'll take your picture.

41:59.684 --> 42:01.402
- And that's my daughter.

42:02.603 --> 42:03.820
Come on.

42:26.085 --> 42:27.587
- He just stays
in his little bubble.

42:31.966 --> 42:33.434
- Sophie?

42:36.721 --> 42:38.638
- Two months.

42:38.639 --> 42:40.474
- What made you start?

42:40.475 --> 42:41.683
- An accident.

42:41.684 --> 42:43.852
- With the iron?

42:43.853 --> 42:45.604
- Cigarette.

42:45.605 --> 42:47.189
- Was it an accident?

42:47.190 --> 42:48.440
- I guess not.

42:48.441 --> 42:49.818
- Go on.

42:52.737 --> 42:54.080
- I-it...

42:55.198 --> 42:56.825
It concentrated me...

42:58.409 --> 43:01.959
To the exclusion
of everything else.

43:03.122 --> 43:04.874
- And that was good?

43:05.875 --> 43:08.085
- It was like a drug.

43:08.086 --> 43:09.713
- What's everything else?

43:15.259 --> 43:17.478
The world has just become...

43:19.263 --> 43:21.857
So inhuman.

43:24.393 --> 43:26.520
Everyone's plugged in.

43:26.521 --> 43:29.981
Blindingly inarticulate.

43:29.982 --> 43:32.609
Obsessed with money,
their careers.

43:32.610 --> 43:35.534
Stupidly, arrogantly content.

43:36.656 --> 43:38.124
I can't talk to them.

43:39.242 --> 43:40.909
I fight them.

43:40.910 --> 43:43.870
I want to destroy them, even.

43:43.871 --> 43:45.831
<i>I crave interaction.</i>

43:45.832 --> 43:47.300
I crave it.

43:48.501 --> 43:51.461
But you just can't anymore.

43:51.462 --> 43:54.591
They pull their devices out
for every little thing:

43:54.592 --> 43:56.886
to reinforce their petty,
convenient notions,

43:56.887 --> 43:58.555
to decide where
they're going to shop,

43:58.556 --> 44:01.306
what they're gonna eat,
what movies they're gonna watch,

44:01.307 --> 44:02.556
everything they ingest.

44:02.557 --> 44:04.355
- Why does that upset you?

44:05.643 --> 44:06.643
- Because what is left?

44:06.644 --> 44:08.061
My God.

44:08.062 --> 44:10.360
- But that doesn't
have to be you.

44:10.361 --> 44:11.439
- Okay.

44:13.693 --> 44:15.944
It's like this is all a game

44:15.945 --> 44:18.664
and I haven't been told
what the rules are.

44:18.665 --> 44:21.366
Or even worse, if I had,

44:21.367 --> 44:23.085
I am ill-equipped
to follow them.

44:24.120 --> 44:25.872
All I can do is provoke.

44:26.998 --> 44:28.915
I become spiteful.

44:30.585 --> 44:32.258
I'm just as bad as they are.

44:32.259 --> 44:34.921
They?
I'm-I'm worse.

44:34.922 --> 44:38.800
I fucking hate myself for it

44:40.595 --> 44:44.598
I'm-I am so fucking lonely.

44:47.185 --> 44:49.603
Why is the world so base?

44:49.604 --> 44:50.981
Why is it so insensitive?

44:50.982 --> 44:52.564
Why is it so selfish?

44:52.565 --> 44:53.732
Why am I?

44:58.654 --> 45:01.948
I am not for this world.

45:05.036 --> 45:06.786
- Fucking shit.

45:06.787 --> 45:09.998
- You've been asleep
a long time.

45:09.999 --> 45:11.208
- How long?

45:11.209 --> 45:13.303
- From when they say
you come in last night?

45:13.304 --> 45:14.762
14 hour.

45:19.008 --> 45:20.175
- Seriously?

45:20.176 --> 45:22.427
- It ain't up to me.

45:22.428 --> 45:24.226
- But you could undo them,
couldn't you?

45:24.227 --> 45:25.722
Extricate my ass?

45:25.723 --> 45:27.766
- And lose my job?

45:27.767 --> 45:28.892
- Where you going?

45:28.893 --> 45:30.060
- Other patient.

45:30.061 --> 45:31.404
- I'm just hungry
like a motherfucker.

45:31.405 --> 45:34.564
- We're gonna get you food,
bring you water.

45:34.565 --> 45:36.283
- You got some crack
I can smoke?

45:36.284 --> 45:37.692
- Afraid not.

45:37.693 --> 45:39.778
- You know, just a little bit.

45:39.779 --> 45:41.531
Fire that shit up.

45:43.074 --> 45:46.117
Motherfucker!

45:46.118 --> 45:48.703
Motherfucker!

45:48.704 --> 45:50.126
Fuck you!

45:51.082 --> 45:52.415
Fuck you!

45:52.416 --> 45:53.833
Fuck you!

45:53.834 --> 45:55.802
Fuck you!
Fuck it!

45:58.256 --> 46:00.554
<i>- We were just out of school.</i>

46:02.510 --> 46:04.719
Living uptown.

46:04.720 --> 46:06.596
We both had really lucrative
job offers.

46:06.597 --> 46:09.391
She was gonna
maybe go to London.

46:09.392 --> 46:12.612
Chose the Far East
instead to be with me.

46:14.021 --> 46:17.571
The next logical step
was marriage and kids.

46:19.527 --> 46:24.158
And we just did that, kind of
without even discussing it.

46:25.408 --> 46:28.660
Two hyper-educated young adults

46:28.661 --> 46:30.500
making the most significant
decision in life

46:30.501 --> 46:32.874
without a single
real conversation.

46:35.126 --> 46:36.878
We talked about movies we saw

46:36.879 --> 46:39.676
more than the meaning
of a future together.

46:42.883 --> 46:45.557
I remember being, um...

46:47.221 --> 46:48.973
What would the word be?

46:50.891 --> 46:54.612
Frozen when she was pregnant
the first time.

46:56.981 --> 46:59.899
I thought,

46:59.900 --> 47:01.402
"Oh.

47:02.445 --> 47:05.574
You know,
something's definitely over."

47:06.574 --> 47:09.242
And I never stopped to enjoy it.

47:09.243 --> 47:11.291
- But you like having kids.

47:12.705 --> 47:15.208
- I love having kids.

47:18.044 --> 47:21.389
I get home, you know,
usually too late for dinner.

47:22.423 --> 47:23.424
<i>She's...</i>

47:24.717 --> 47:27.093
Into her third drink,

47:27.094 --> 47:29.768
and I have about an hour before
the girls have to go to bed,

47:29.769 --> 47:31.348
and I-

47:31.349 --> 47:34.899
I go into their room with
a plate, and I-l don't leave.

47:39.231 --> 47:40.778
Most of our interactions
these days

47:40.779 --> 47:45.737
consist of algebra and whatever

47:45.738 --> 47:48.034
self-consciously
multi-cultural book

47:48.035 --> 47:49.579
they're reading at the time.

47:53.037 --> 47:54.710
As they get older, they get...

47:56.582 --> 47:57.629
Quieter.

48:00.002 --> 48:03.088
The older one, Allie, she's-
she's getting belligerent.

48:03.089 --> 48:04.090
- Mm.

48:05.424 --> 48:07.802
Your wife drinks
'cause you're not really there.

48:14.183 --> 48:16.231
- Yeah, that's obviously
part of that.

48:21.482 --> 48:24.326
- Not exactly the raucous time
we were thinking of, huh?

48:27.988 --> 48:29.906
- It's honest.

48:29.907 --> 48:31.241
- That's ironic.

48:31.242 --> 48:32.243
- Mm.

48:40.543 --> 48:42.216
- I don't want to go home yet.

48:44.004 --> 48:45.677
- You have to, Sam.

48:53.973 --> 48:56.349
- Just one more day.

48:56.350 --> 48:58.193
She's not expecting me yet.

49:07.945 --> 49:09.367
- One more day.

49:11.490 --> 49:13.743
- Are there friends
you can speak to?

49:13.744 --> 49:14.909
Your father?

49:14.910 --> 49:17.328
Your brother.
Hal, isn't it?

49:17.329 --> 49:19.876
- What is this with me
needing to talk to anyone?

49:19.877 --> 49:22.423
- Just to know others are
concerned, care about you.

49:22.424 --> 49:24.586
- You believe that?

49:24.587 --> 49:27.130
That people
care about each other'?

49:27.131 --> 49:29.509
- We treat people the way
we want to be treated.

49:29.510 --> 49:31.134
It's just compassion.

49:31.135 --> 49:33.604
- I don't consider myself
compassionate.

49:34.597 --> 49:36.019
I have no respect for my father

49:36.020 --> 49:39.225
because he is bossed around
by my mother.

49:39.226 --> 49:42.270
Now, I not only hate her,

49:42.271 --> 49:45.857
but I resent her

49:45.858 --> 49:49.319
because it's interfering
with my life.

49:49.320 --> 49:51.362
- All this is natural.

49:51.363 --> 49:53.490
- It's-

49:53.491 --> 49:55.909
Pretty fucked up too.

49:55.910 --> 49:57.494
- You're young.

49:57.495 --> 49:59.791
You don't want your life
interrupted.

49:59.792 --> 50:01.790
- I love her so much.

50:06.337 --> 50:07.837
- Hello, Joe.

50:07.838 --> 50:10.006
- Fucking let me out of here.

50:10.007 --> 50:12.929
- In about 20 hours, you'll
be able to sign yourself out.

50:12.930 --> 50:14.804
- So let's skip
the fucking hassle.

50:14.805 --> 50:18.598
- By law, I've got to hold you
for 48 hours.

50:18.599 --> 50:21.351
- Hold a man that wasn't
hurting nobody.

50:21.352 --> 50:23.770
Come to his apartment uninvited,

50:23.771 --> 50:26.149
chuck him in a hospital,
strap him down.

50:28.359 --> 50:31.659
- If you could kill yourself
right now, would you?

50:33.656 --> 50:35.490
Ain't gonna kill myself.

50:35.491 --> 50:36.868
- You'll be dead in a year.

50:36.869 --> 50:38.456
- You told me that last year.

50:38.457 --> 50:40.248
- Last year
I gave you two years.

50:40.249 --> 50:41.666
We're right on schedule.

50:41.667 --> 50:43.665
- Tell that nurse
to bring me my dinner.

50:43.666 --> 50:44.666
- Not until I-

50:44.667 --> 50:46.635
- I don't think you understand.

50:46.636 --> 50:49.847
You are not here anymore.

50:57.304 --> 50:59.227
<i>- That what you're expecting,
Mr. Clancy?</i>

50:59.228 --> 51:01.266
- It's opening up.

51:01.267 --> 51:02.735
- You want to try
something else?

51:02.736 --> 51:04.185
- I'm good, thanks.

51:04.186 --> 51:05.478
- Hello, Jeffrey.

51:05.479 --> 51:07.855
- You too?

51:07.856 --> 51:08.856
Where's Devlin?

51:08.857 --> 51:10.358
- He's here.
- The full team.

51:10.359 --> 51:11.484
- Care to join me?

51:11.485 --> 51:13.194
- Think we can be nice
to each other?

51:13.195 --> 51:14.196
- I'm optimistic.

51:15.864 --> 51:17.282
- Excuse me.

51:17.283 --> 51:18.866
- His name's Jerry.

51:18.867 --> 51:20.994
- First name basis.

51:20.995 --> 51:23.329
- Hey, Jerry, this is Rachel.
- Yeah.

51:23.330 --> 51:24.581
- I'm arguing against her
in the morning.

51:24.582 --> 51:26.124
Make sure she's hungover.

